# Approach
1. Split number into an array by converting it into a string and the split methods.
2. By default, set all numbers to be true. 
3. Use a for loop to iterate through the array. 
4. For each loop, get the length of the filtered array - count. 
5. Filter the array to find if the string 'x' is equal to stringified index 'i'. 
6. If count does not equal the value at arr[i], switch isValid to false and break the loop. 
7. return isValid


```
/**
 * @param {string} num
 * @return {boolean}
 */
var digitCount = function(num) {
    const arr = num.toString().split('');
    let isValid = true;

    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        const count = arr.filter((x) => x === i.toString()).length;
        if (count !== parseInt(arr[i])) {
            isValid = false;
            break;
        }
    }

    return isValid;
};

```

