# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The code aims to check if a given string num satisfies a specific condition where each digit i must occur exactly i times in the string. If this condition is met for every digit, the function returns true; otherwise, it returns false. The code uses a HashMap to count the occurrences of each digit in the string and compares the counts with the expected values.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Check if the first character of the string is '0'. If it is, return false because '0' cannot be the first character if every digit should occur at least once.

2. Initialize a HashMap<Integer, Integer> called map to store the counts of each digit.

3. Iterate through each character ch in the string num:

4. Calculate the numeric value k of the current character by subtracting '0' from it.
Update the count of digit k in the map by using map.put(k, map.getOrDefault(k, 0) + 1).
Iterate through the indices i from 0 to n-1, where n is the length of the string num:

5. Calculate the numeric value m of the digit at index i in num.
Check if m is equal to the count of digit i in the map using map.getOrDefault(i, 0).
If m is not equal to the expected count, return false.
If the code reaches this point without returning false, it means that the condition is satisfied for every digit, so return true.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
The code iterates through the string num twice, once to count the occurrences of each digit and once to check if the counts match the expected values. Therefore, the time complexity is O(2n), which simplifies to O(n), where n is the length of the input string num.
- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
The code uses a HashMap to store the counts of digits, which can have a maximum of 10 entries (0 to 9). Therefore, the space complexity is O(10), which simplifies to O(1) as it's a constant space requirement.
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean digitCount(String num) {
        if (num.charAt(0) == '0') return false;

        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        int n = num.length();

        for (char ch : num.toCharArray()){
            int k = ch - '0';
            map.put(k, map.getOrDefault(k, 0) + 1);
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            int m = num.charAt(i) - '0';
            if (m != map.getOrDefault(i, 0)){
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
}
```
