# Intuition 
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The brute force will result in O(n^2) time complexity so to minimise it we apply binary search within the outer loop to search for start of the element where the target or the success is achieved.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Sort the array first to apply the binary search since we only need the count. And then search for the element idx for each spell where after which the success is achieved in the array. Now simply add the count in the ans array and return it.

