# Intuition
Main observation: we always cut <b>straight whole line</b> which splits rectangle into two. It gives fuel to DP solution over $m,n$: what is the maximal price we can get out of $$m*n$$ rectangle? We just try exact match in prices, each vertical and horizontal cut, and choose maximum option.
DP formula: $f(m,n)=max(f(m,x)+f(m,n-x)_{1<=x<n},f(x,n)+f(m-x,n)_{1<=x<m},price(m,n))$

# Approach
Implement DP formula + use memoization via `@cache`. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(m*n*(m+n))`
- Space complexity: `O(m*n)`

# Code
```
class Solution:
    def sellingWood(self, m: int, n: int, prices: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        prices=defaultdict(int)|{(h,w):p for h,w,p in prices}
        @cache
        def f(m,n):            
            hor = max((f(x,n)+f(m-x,n) for x in range(1,1+m//2)), default=0)
            ver = max((f(m,x)+f(m,n-x) for x in range(1,1+n//2)), default=0)
            return max(hor,ver, prices[m,n])
        return f(m,n)


