solutions.content:
**UPVOTE IF HELPFuuL**

A long question but just implementation.

* Firstly create a **2-D** array with all values initialised to```-1``` so if linked list is incomplete, we will not update remaining index of array as they will already be ```-1```.

* With a while loop put the value from linked list at index ```[x][y]``` -> ```res[x][y] = head -> val;```

**HOW TO UPDATE VALUES OF X,Y**
Variables:
* **r1** -> represents TOPMOST row that has been filled
* **r2** -> represents BOTTOM row that has been filled
* **c1** -> represents LEFTMOST column that has been filled
* **c2** -> represents RIGHTMOST column that has been filled

* **left** -> true if we are moving in LEFT direction.
* **right** ->true if we are moving in RIGHT direction.
* **down** -> true if we are moving in DOWN direction.
* If all three are **false** we are moing in upward direction.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/a5639faf-ea4a-416f-925f-1ab9120b55ee_1656828246.234272.png)

* While moving right -> keep increasing **Y** -> when at last point, increase **r1**.
* While moving down -> keep increasing **X** -> when at last point . decrease **c2**.
* While moving left -> keep decreasing **Y** -> when at last point, decrease **r2**.
* While moving upward -> keep decreasing **X** -> when at last point, increase **c1**.

ALSO REMEMBER TO CHANGE ```bool left, right, down``` accordingly while reaching last point in any direction.


**UPVOTE IF HELPFuuL**
```

class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> spiralMatrix(int m, int n, ListNode* head) {

        vector<vector<int>> res;
        for (int i=0; i<m; i++){
            vector<int> k;
            for (int j=0; j<n; j++){
                k.push_back(-1);
            }
            res.push_back(k);
        }
        int r1=-1, r2=m, c1=-1, c2=n;
        int x=0, y=0;
        bool right=true, down=false, left=false;

        while (head){

            res[x][y] = head -> val;
            head = head -> next;

            if (right){
                if (y+1 == c2){
                    x++;
                    right = false;
                    down = true;
                    r1++;
                }else{
                    y++;
                }
            }
            else if(down){
                if (x+1==r2){
                    y--;
                    down = false;
                    left = true;
                    c2--;
                }else{
                    x++;
                }
            }
            else if(left){
                if (y-1==c1){
                    x--;
                    left = false;
                    r2--;
                }else{
                    y--;
                }
            }
            else{
                if (x-1==r1){
                    y++;
                    right = true;
                    c1++;
                }else{
                    x--;
                }
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
